---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout region="na" title="About">
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Hero -->
      <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.3fr)_minmax(0,1.1fr)] items-start">
        <div class="max-w-3xl rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 text-slate-900 shadow-2xl">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-[#B48A3C] px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white">
            Alturascope North America
          </span>
          <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
            About Alturascope
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base text-slate-600">
            Alturascope is a specialised site-reality partner for landlords, funds, and occupiers across
            the U.S. and Canada. We turn messy, real-world spaces into clear, decision-ready visuals and
            reports you can trust for design, budgeting, and approvals.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5 shadow-md transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:bg-accent/10 max-w-sm ml-auto">
          <img
            src="/images/attic.jpg"
            onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/Images/attic.jpg';"
            alt="Attic space with exposed structure and services documented by Alturascope"
            loading="lazy"
            class="h-56 w-full object-cover sm:h-64 lg:h-72"
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <section class="mt-6">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-5 py-4 text-sm text-slate-800 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <p class="font-medium">
            Why this work is a good use of funds
          </p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-slate-700">
            Our as-built surveys are designed to be a small line item that protects the big ones: design fees, construction spend, lease commitments, and opening dates. They turn “we think” into “we know” before you commit.
            <a href="/why-as-built-surveys-matter" class="ml-1 font-medium text-[#0F2A43] underline underline-offset-2">
              Read the full reasoning.
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <!-- Quick stats -->
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
          Nationwide U.S. &amp; Canada coverage
        </div>
        <div class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
          Flight-pass model for fast mobilisation
        </div>
        <div class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
          Digital twin + detailed report on every visit
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- What we do cards -->
      <div class="mt-10">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
          What we do
        </h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
              As-Built Site Reality
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
              One visit to capture how a space truly is today so design and budgets start from reality,
              not assumptions.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-xs text-slate-700">
              <li>Digital twin and photo storyboard</li>
              <li>Fixture &amp; services counts</li>
              <li>Detailed conditions report with upsides &amp; concerns</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
              Construction Progress
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
              Independent eyes on your build so pay apps, change orders, and hand-over decisions are grounded in evidence.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-xs text-slate-700">
              <li>Fixed-route progress photos &amp; notes</li>
              <li>Issues &amp; exceptions log</li>
              <li>Reality-check against programme and draws</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-slate-900">
              Portfolio &amp; Lease Diligence
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
              Comparable reality checks across multiple buildings so you can shortlist, renew, or relocate with confidence.
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-xs text-slate-700">
              <li>Like-for-like site summaries</li>
              <li>Access, loading, and context call-outs</li>
              <li>Red flags and hidden-cost indicators</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:bg-accent/10">
            <img
              src="/images/Fire%20safety.jpg"
              onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/Images/Fire%20safety.jpg';"
              alt="Fire safety and mechanical room example"
              loading="lazy"
              class="w-full h-48 object-cover block"
            >
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:bg-accent/10">
            <img
              src="/images/WhatsApp%20Image%202025-11-24%20at%2020.21.02_1f2282c2.jpg"
              onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/Images/WhatsApp%20Image%202025-11-24%20at%2020.21.02_1f2282c2.jpg';"
              alt="High-rise building under construction in city centre"
              loading="lazy"
              class="w-full h-48 object-cover block"
            >
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:bg-accent/10">
            <img
              src="/Images/SING0469.JPG"
              onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/images/SING0469.JPG';"
              alt="Construction progress photo"
              loading="lazy"
              class="w-full h-48 object-cover block"
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- How we work -->
      <div class="mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
          How we work
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
          Simple, repeatable steps on every engagement.
        </p>
        <ol class="mt-4 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-4">
          <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-sm text-slate-700 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">01. Scope</p>
            <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-slate-900">Clarify the decision</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs">
              We align on what you’re deciding (renew, relocate, fund, phase, etc.) and what
              your team needs to see in order to move.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-sm text-slate-700 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">02. Mobilise</p>
            <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-slate-900">Lock dates &amp; access</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs">
              Using a national flight pass, we book travel, coordinate with building management,
              and confirm any out-of-hours requirements.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-sm text-slate-700 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">03. Capture</p>
            <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-slate-900">Walk, measure, record</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs">
              On site we follow a disciplined route, capturing structure, services, access and
              anything likely to affect design, cost, or schedule.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-4 text-sm text-slate-700 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">04. Deliver</p>
            <p class="mt-1 font-medium text-slate-900">Turn into decisions</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-xs">
              You receive a digital twin, labelled photos, and a detailed report with fixture counts,
              a high-level mechanical overview, and prioritised recommendations.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <!-- Coverage & turnarounds + What you receive -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.3fr)_minmax(0,2fr)]">
        <!-- Coverage -->
        <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-6 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-700">
            Coverage &amp; turnarounds
          </h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <li>Nationwide coverage across the U.S. &amp; Canada</li>
            <li>Travel underpinned by an unlimited flight pass for predictable mobilisation</li>
            <li>Standard delivery window typically within a few business days of site access</li>
            <li>Rush, evening, and weekend options where timelines are tight</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <!-- What you receive every time -->
        <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-700">
            What you receive every time
          </h2>
          <div class="mt-3 grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>Digital twin or 360° walkthrough of the space</li>
              <li>Photo storyboard labelled by area and topic</li>
              <li>Counts for key fixtures and services</li>
              <li>Notes on access, loading, vertical transport, and neighbors</li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <li>
                Detailed written report with fixture counts and a high-level mechanical / services overview
              </li>
              <li>Upside opportunities and concerns clearly highlighted</li>
              <li>Recommendations prioritised (P1 / P2 / P3) so teams know what to act on first</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
      <!-- Who we serve & Standards/Leadership -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.4fr)_minmax(0,1.6fr)]">
        <!-- Who we serve -->
        <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-700">
            Who we serve
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-700">
            Alturascope is built for teams who make decisions on space at scale:
          </p>
          <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1">Landlords &amp; asset managers</span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1">Office &amp; workplace teams</span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1">Retail &amp; clinic roll-outs</span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1">Private equity &amp; lenders</span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1">Design-build &amp; GC partners</span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-500">
            Typical use cases include pre-lease diligence, renewal vs. relocation decisions,
            expansion programmes, and independent progress verification.
          </p>
        </article>
        <!-- Standards & leadership as two mini-cards -->
        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-5 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-700">
              Our standards
            </h3>
            <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-xs text-slate-700">
              <li>No “clipboard tourism” – every visit is scoped against a clear decision.</li>
              <li>Consistent capture routes so multi-site data lines up like-for-like.</li>
              <li>Clear separation of fact, risk, and opinion in every report.</li>
              <li>Calm, professional conduct on site – we represent your brand.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
            <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-700">
              <button
                id="leadership-photo-trigger"
                type="button"
                class="inline-flex h-10 w-10 overflow-hidden rounded-full border border-slate-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-accent"
                aria-label="Enlarge leadership photo"
              >
                <img
                  src="/Images/APH%20image.jpg"
                  onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/images/APH%20image.jpg';"
                  alt="Alturascope leadership"
                  class="h-full w-full object-cover"
                >
              </button>
              <span>Leadership</span>
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-slate-700">
              Alturascope is led by Andrew Harris, a hands-on site specialist with deep experience in
              commercial fit-outs across the U.K., U.S., and Canada. Andrew brings a mix of practical
              trades knowledge and years of surveying complex office, retail, and clinic spaces for
              landlords, funds, and occupiers.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-700">
              The goal is simple: translate on-the-ground reality into clear, decision-ready outputs for
              teams who don’t have the time to walk every site themselves.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Leadership image modal -->
      <div
        id="leadership-photo-modal"
        class="fixed inset-0 z-40 hidden flex items-center justify-center bg-black/60 px-4"
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <div class="relative w-full max-w-sm rounded-2xl bg-white p-4 shadow-2xl">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="absolute right-3 top-3 rounded-full bg-black/70 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-white hover:bg-black"
            data-close-leadership-modal
          >
            Close
          </button>
          <img
            src="/Images/APH%20image.jpg"
            onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/images/APH%20image.jpg';"
            alt="Alturascope leadership"
            class="w-full max-h-[60vh] rounded-xl object-cover"
          >
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA strip -->
      <div class="mt-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-6 py-8 sm:flex sm:items-center sm:justify-between transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:ring-2 hover:ring-accent/30 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
            Ready to move a site forward?
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Share the address, your decision point, and your timeline. We’ll confirm the scope,
            recommend the right visit type, and send a simple, all-in quote.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3 sm:mt-0 sm:justify-end">
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-slate-900 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-slate-800"
          >
            Book a visit
          </a>
          <a
            href="/pricing"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-slate-800 hover:bg-white"
          >
            View pricing
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<script>
  if (typeof window !== "undefined") {
    window.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
      const trigger = document.getElementById("leadership-photo-trigger");
      const modal = document.getElementById("leadership-photo-modal");
      const closeButtons = document.querySelectorAll("[data-close-leadership-modal]");

      if (!trigger || !modal) return;

      const closeModal = () => {
        modal.classList.add("hidden");
      };

      trigger.addEventListener("click", () => {
        modal.classList.remove("hidden");
        modal.setAttribute("aria-hidden", "false");
      });

      closeButtons.forEach((btn) => {
        btn.addEventListener("click", closeModal);
      });

      modal.addEventListener("click", (event) => {
        if (event.target === modal) {
          closeModal();
        }
      });

      window.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
        if (event.key === "Escape" && !modal.classList.contains("hidden")) {
          closeModal();
        }
      });
    });
  }
</script>
